George, and other's into the "retro look"

Avoid at all costs the chrome headlamp anti glare sheilds--they rust
like there is no tomorrow--the better ones are stainless, and are redily
available at any finer truck stop---the "Large Cars" use them a lot--

Also beware---

These things radiate a bunch of heat off the headlamp bulbs right back
into the lamp--and the bulbs / filiments life is very short with these
"cool" sheilds.

Been there, done it, got pissed, removed them.

But they still look neat--:>)


Later, 

Terry

 
